quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,6,"As to the infidels, alike is it to them whether thou warn them or warn them not - they will not believe"
  2,7,"Their hearts and their ears hath God sealed up; and over their eyes is a covering. For them, a severe chastisement"
  2,8,"And some here are who say, \"We believe in God, and in the latter day:\" Yet are they not believers"
  2,9,"Fain would they deceive God and those who have believed; but they deceive themselves only, and know it not"
  2,10,"Diseased are their hearts! And that disease hath God increased creased to them. Their's a sore chastisement, for that they treated their prophet as a liar"
  2,11,"And when it is said to them, \"Cause not disorders in the earth:\" they say, \"Nay, rather do we set them right"
  2,12,Is it not that they are themselves the authors of disorder? But they perceive it not
  2,13,"And when it is said to them, \"Believe as other men have believed;\" they say, \"Shall we believe as the fools have believed?\" Is it not that they are themselves the fools? But they know it not"
  2,14,"And when they meet the faithful they say, \"We believe;\" but when they are apart with their Satans they say, \"Verily we hold with you, and at them we only mock"
  2,15,"God shall mock at them, and keep them long in their rebellion, wandering in perplexity"
  2,16,"These are they who have purchased error at the price of guidance: but their traffic hath not been gainful, neither are they guided at all"